Citation.sTitle: Effect of temperature on the process of preferential solvation of 1,4-dioxane and 12-crown-4 ethers in the mixture of water with formamide
Citation.sAbstract: The dissolution enthalpy of 1,4-dioxane and 12-crown-4 ethers in the mixture of water (W) and formamide (F) was measured at four temperatures: 293.15 K, 298.15 K, 303.15 K, 308.15 K. The standard molar enthalpy of solution, , depends on the size of cyclic ethers and on temperature. The values of become more negative with increasing molecule size and they increase with increasing temperature. The effect of temperature on the process of preferential solvation of cyclic ethers has been discussed.
